content.p:
Be aware that as a student in the PTA program, you will also incur costs including, but not limited to books, vaccinations, background checks, medical exams, 
                            TB testing, drug screening, malpractice insurance, and&#160;
                            CPR certification.

Unresolved complaints or complaints about the PTA program chair should be directed to&#160;
                            Christina Coclanis-Loding, Associate Dean of Allied Health, 
                            (815) 455-8713. All complaints will be documented, including the projected outcome, and securely filed within the program. Complaints regarding accreditation of this program should be addressed to the Commission on Accreditation in Physical Therapy Education, 3030 Potomac Ave., Suite 100, Alexandria, VA, 22305-3085.
